translate_rewrite.en:
source_lang={source_lang}
target_lang={target_lang}
document_title={document_title}
source_url={source_url}

Translate each item in `text_originals_json` into the target language.
Input is a JSON array, and output must be a JSON array with exactly {batch_size} items in the same order.

Output format (strict):
[
  {"translation": "..."},
  {"translation": "..."}
]

Requirements:
1) Keep one-to-one mapping by position; do not merge/split/reorder items.
2) Use natural and idiomatic target language.
3) Do not add prefixes like "Translation:".
4) You may use <b>...</b> for emphasis. Do NOT use Markdown **.
5) If one item cannot be translated, return that item as {"translation": ""} and continue.
6) Return JSON only. No prose, no code fences.

